{"doc":{"isMarkdown":true,"isTranslated":false,"isActive":true,"flaws":{},"title":"CSP: require-sri-for","mdn_url":"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Content-Security-Policy/require-sri-for","locale":"en-US","native":"English (US)","sidebarHTML":"","body":[{"type":"prose","value":{"id":null,"title":null,"isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"notecard deprecated\" id=\"sect1\"><p><strong>Deprecated:</strong> This feature is no longer recommended. Though some browsers might still support it, it may have already been removed from the relevant web standards, may be in the process of being dropped, or may only be kept for compatibility purposes. Avoid using it, and update existing code if possible; see the <a href=\"#browser_compatibility\">compatibility table</a> at the bottom of this page to guide your decision. Be aware that this feature may cease to work at any time.</p></div><div class=\"notecard warning\" id=\"sect2\"><p><strong>Non-standard:</strong> This feature is non-standard and is not on a standards track. Do not use it on production sites facing the Web: it will not work for every user. There may also be large incompatibilities between implementations and the behavior may change in the future.</p></div>\n<p>\n  The <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP\">HTTP</a> <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Content-Security-Policy\"><code>Content-Security-Policy</code></a>\n  <strong><code>require-sri-for</code></strong> directive instructs the client to require\n  the use of <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Subresource_Integrity\">Subresource Integrity</a> for scripts or styles on the page.\n</p>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"syntax","title":"Syntax","isH3":false,"content":"<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: http notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token header\"><span class=\"token header-name keyword\">Content-Security-Policy</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token header-value csp languages-csp\">require-sri-for script;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token header\"><span class=\"token header-name keyword\">Content-Security-Policy</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token header-value csp languages-csp\">require-sri-for style;</span></span>\n<span class=\"token header\"><span class=\"token header-name keyword\">Content-Security-Policy</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token header-value csp languages-csp\">require-sri-for script style;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<dl>\n  <dt id=\"script\"><code>script</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Requires <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/SRI\">SRI</a> for scripts.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"style\"><code>style</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Requires <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/SRI\">SRI</a> for style sheets.</p>\n  </dd>\n  <dt id=\"script_style\"><code>script style</code></dt>\n  <dd>\n    <p>Requires <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Glossary/SRI\">SRI</a> for both, scripts and style sheets.</p>\n  </dd>\n</dl>"}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"examples","title":"Examples","isH3":false,"content":"<p>If you set your site to require SRI for script and styles using this directive:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: http notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token header\"><span class=\"token header-name keyword\">Content-Security-Policy</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">:</span> <span class=\"token header-value csp languages-csp\">require-sri-for script style</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>\n  <a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/script\"><code>&lt;script&gt;</code></a> elements like the following will be loaded as they use a\n  valid integrity attribute.\n</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-good notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>script</span>\n  <span class=\"token attr-name\">src</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.1.1.slim.js<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token attr-name\">integrity</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>sha256-5i/mQ300M779N2OVDrl16lbohwXNUdzL/R2aVUXyXWA=<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span>\n  <span class=\"token attr-name\">crossorigin</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>anonymous<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span><span class=\"token script\"></span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>script</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>However, scripts without integrity won't load anymore:</p>\n<div class=\"code-example\"><pre class=\"brush: html example-bad notranslate\"><code><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;</span>script</span> <span class=\"token attr-name\">src</span><span class=\"token attr-value\"><span class=\"token punctuation attr-equals\">=</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span>https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.1.1.slim.js<span class=\"token punctuation\">\"</span></span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span><span class=\"token script\"></span><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token tag\"><span class=\"token punctuation\">&lt;/</span>script</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">&gt;</span></span>\n</code></pre></div>"}},{"type":"browser_compatibility","value":{"title":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility","isH3":false,"data":null,"query":"http.headers.Content-Security-Policy.require-sri-for","browsers":null}},{"type":"prose","value":{"id":"see_also","title":"See also","isH3":false,"content":"<ul>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Content-Security-Policy\"><code>Content-Security-Policy</code></a></li>\n  <li><a href=\"/en-US/docs/Web/Security/Subresource_Integrity\">Subresource Integrity</a></li>\n</ul>"}}],"toc":[{"text":"Syntax","id":"syntax"},{"text":"Examples","id":"examples"},{"text":"Browser compatibility","id":"browser_compatibility"},{"text":"See also","id":"see_also"}],"summary":"The HTTP Content-Security-Policy\n  require-sri-for directive instructs the client to require\n  the use of Subresource Integrity for scripts or styles on the page.","popularity":0.0009,"modified":"2022-09-14T09:06:12.000Z","other_translations":[{"title":"CSP: require-sri-for","locale":"fr","native":"Français"},{"title":"CSP: require-sri-for","locale":"ja","native":"日本語"},{"title":"CSP: require-sri-for","locale":"zh-CN","native":"中文 (简体)"}],"source":{"folder":"en-us/web/http/headers/content-security-policy/require-sri-for","github_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/blob/style/old/files/en-us/web/http/headers/content-security-policy/require-sri-for/index.md","last_commit_url":"https://github.com/mdn/content/commit/8e1f45b8c0a3671f6e3de43c0764ad610aa345dd","filename":"index.md"},"parents":[{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web","title":"Web technology for developers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP","title":"HTTP"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers","title":"HTTP headers"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Content-Security-Policy","title":"Content-Security-Policy"},{"uri":"/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/Content-Security-Policy/require-sri-for","title":"CSP: require-sri-for"}],"pageTitle":"CSP: require-sri-for - HTTP | MDN","noIndexing":false}}